## What to do
Create a PdsRecordService that performs RBAC-gated CRUD operations on org repos.

### PdsRecordService class
```typescript
export class PdsRecordService {
  constructor(
    pdsAdminService: PdsAdminService,
    orgStore: OrgStore,
    auditLogger: AuditLogger
  )

  // Create a record in an org's repo
  // 1. Check RBAC: caller must have 'contributor' or 'admin' role
  // 2. Get org session via PdsAdminService
  // 3. Call com.atproto.repo.createRecord via XRPC as the org account
  // 4. Log audit event
  async createRecord(orgId: string, callerDid: string, params: {
    collection: string,  // e.g., 'org.certified.hypercert'
    record: unknown,     // the record data (any Lexicon)
    rkey?: string        // optional record key
  }): Promise<{ uri: string, cid: string }>

  // Get a record from an org's repo (no RBAC needed — ATProto repos are public)
  async getRecord(orgDid: string, collection: string, rkey: string): Promise<unknown>

  // Update a record in an org's repo
  // 1. Check RBAC: caller must have 'contributor' or 'admin' role
  // 2. Get org session
  // 3. Call com.atproto.repo.putRecord
  async putRecord(orgId: string, callerDid: string, params: {
    collection: string,
    rkey: string,
    record: unknown,
    swapRecord?: string  // CID for optimistic concurrency
  }): Promise<{ uri: string, cid: string }>

  // Delete a record from an org's repo
  // 1. Check RBAC: caller must have 'admin' role (only admins can delete)
  // 2. Get org session
  // 3. Call com.atproto.repo.deleteRecord
  async deleteRecord(orgId: string, callerDid: string, params: {
    collection: string,
    rkey: string,
    swapRecord?: string
  }): Promise<void>

  // List records in an org's repo (no RBAC needed — public)
  async listRecords(orgDid: string, collection: string, opts?: {
    limit?: number,
    cursor?: string,
    reverse?: boolean
  }): Promise<{ records: unknown[], cursor?: string }>
}
```

### XRPC calls
Use @atproto/api's AtpAgent, authenticated with the org's session:
```typescript
const agent = new AtpAgent({ service: pdsUrl })
agent.session = await pdsAdminService.getOrgSession(orgId)
await agent.com.atproto.repo.createRecord({ repo: orgDid, collection, record })
```

## Don't
- Skip RBAC checks on any write operation
- Allow viewers to create/update/delete records
- Allow contributors to delete records (admin only)
- Cache org sessions indefinitely (sessions expire — refresh as needed)
- Expose the org's credentials or session tokens to the caller

