## What to do

### PdsAdminService — Org account lifecycle
Manages creating/deleting PDS accounts for organizations.

```typescript
class PdsAdminService {
  constructor(pdsUrl: string, pdsDomain: string, credentialStore: CredentialStore, orgStore: OrgStore)

  async createOrgAccount(orgName: string, creatorDid: string): Promise<{ orgId, did, handle }>
  // 1. Generate handle: org-{randomBase36(6)}.{pdsDomain}
  // 2. Generate password: crypto.randomBytes(64).toString('hex')
  // 3. Call com.atproto.server.createAccount via AtpAgent XRPC
  //    - email: org-{uuid}@{pdsDomain} (synthetic, not real)
  //    - handle, password from above
  // 4. Store encrypted password via credentialStore.storePassword(did, password)
  // 5. Create org in orgStore, add creator as admin
  // 6. Return { orgId, did, handle }

  async deleteOrgAccount(orgId: string, callerDid: string): Promise<void>
  // 1. Verify caller is admin via orgStore.canAdmin()
  // 2. Get org's credentials, create session
  // 3. Call com.atproto.server.deleteAccount via XRPC
  // 4. Delete from credentialStore and orgStore

  async getOrgSession(orgId: string): Promise<AtpSessionData>
  // 1. Get org DID from orgStore
  // 2. Get decrypted password from credentialStore
  // 3. Call com.atproto.server.createSession via XRPC
  // 4. Return session data
}
```

### PdsRecordService — RBAC-gated CRUD on org repos
```typescript
class PdsRecordService {
  constructor(pdsAdminService: PdsAdminService, orgStore: OrgStore)

  async createRecord(orgId, callerDid, { collection, record, rkey? }): Promise<{ uri, cid }>
  // Check canWrite → get org session → com.atproto.repo.createRecord

  async getRecord(orgDid, collection, rkey): Promise<unknown>
  // No RBAC needed (ATProto repos are public)

  async putRecord(orgId, callerDid, { collection, rkey, record }): Promise<{ uri, cid }>
  // Check canWrite → get org session → com.atproto.repo.putRecord

  async deleteRecord(orgId, callerDid, { collection, rkey }): Promise<void>
  // Check canAdmin (only admins delete) → get org session → com.atproto.repo.deleteRecord

  async listRecords(orgDid, collection, { limit?, cursor? }): Promise<{ records, cursor? }>
  // No RBAC needed
}
```

All XRPC calls use @atproto/api's AtpAgent, authenticated with the org's session.

## Don't
- Expose org credentials to callers
- Skip RBAC checks on any write operation
- Allow contributors to delete records (admin only)
- Cache sessions indefinitely (they expire)
- Use PDS internal APIs (use XRPC only — external API)
